commit.message: doc: Clean up formatting of Makefiles for documentation

doc: Remove SRM-HOWTO from Makefile clean target for German documentation

There is no German SRM-HOWTO being generated, so no need to remove
it in the clean target of the Makefile for the German documentation.
doc: Fix filename in Makefile clean target for German documentation

doc: Remove generated manpages

The manpages are generated from the SGML files during build.

srmbootfat: Switch manpage generation to docbook-utils

sgmltools-lite and jade are no longer maintained upstream and in
Debian, so switch to docbook-utils which still is supported.

doc: Switch documentation generation to docbook-utils

sgmltools-lite and jade are no longer maintained upstream and in
Debian, so switch to docbook-utils which still is supported.

Drop __KERNEL_STRICT_NAMES checks

The kernel headers don't use this anymore (except on s390 and mips)

zip: Hardcode crc_32_tab[]

It was static already, so we're not saving any binary size by
calculating it at runtime. Might as well compile it it.

tools: Remove big-endian ext2 support

See http://www.linux-m68k.org/ext2swap.html

Mark bootfs[] as static const

Which requires propagating the const qualifier a few places.

fs: Remove isofs declaration

It was unused, which was good because the definition at the bottom of
the file is just called "iso".
Organize prototypes and remove extern keywords
